    "The final prediction b pred is chosen from the candidate set as the best match for the referring expression.",
    "sorted candidate set with non-maximum suppression (NMS) is given by:D ′ (I, Q, C(I)) = Sort NMS(D(I, Q, C(I))), by area(b i) (desc).",
    "(5) After this refinement and sorting stage, each candidate is represented as a tuple (b i, d i), which serves as the foundation for the subsequent grounding process.Candidate Selection After enriching and sorting the candidate set, we directly select the most appropriate candidate from D ref = D ′ (I, Q, C(I)) based solely on its descriptive caption.",
    "For each candidate tuple (b i, d i), the LLM is provided with the query Q, the global context T global, the candidate's bounding box b i, and its detailed description d i.",
